🎨 The literal technique (ground truth)

In painting:
	•	Artists often start with a green/gray underpainting (called verdaccio)
	•	Then layer reds, oranges, and flesh tones on top

Why?
	•	Skin naturally contains:
	•	cool undertones (veins, shadows → green/blue)
	•	warm surface tones (blood, light → reds/oranges)

So:

Green underneath + red on top = believable, living skin

Not flat. Not fake. Alive.

